UNITED STATES of America v. Morris Joseph KESSLER, alias Anthony Mariano, Appellant. No. 9037. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Jan. 9, 1946. Decided Jan. 15, 1946. William A. Gray, of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant. Walter A. Gay, Jr., of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellee.

Before GOODRICH, McLAUGHLIN, and O’CONNELL, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the District Court, 63 F.Supp. 964, is affirmed.
